texts.text: >A few years ago...
>At an American technical institute.
You got the highest scores again, Naoto?!
Of course he did! He's a genius!
Thanks, I'm glad all that effort paid off.
The upperclassmen have even begun to take notice, including myself.
Thank you very much, Shinonome.
Within my research group, I always got the highest scores.
But I'm terrible at everything else. I don't even know how to really hold a conversation.
I even got fired from my part-time job because of that.
All I have is this lab and this group.
This is the only place where I feel like I'm accepted.
Until, SHE came along...
It is my pleasure to welcome in our newest addition to our group.
She graduated high school early and decided to enroll here. Please introduce yourself, Shiori.

I'm Shiori Koden.
I came from Japan.
Any questions?
I... I'm from Japan too. I'm glad you joined us. I hope we can get along.
That isn't really my plan, but fine, as long as I'm having fun.
You're already at the top, Shiori?!
That's incredible! She really is a genius!
Well, duh. No one here comes close to me.
>Naoto began studying even harder after losing to Shiori.
>But no matter what he did, she kept winning...
I'm studying this much. How is it that I can't beat her...?!
>Shiori remained at the top.
>She even began publishing papers and giving talks at conferences.
>Her ideas also garnered the attention of several companies.
>In short order, she would start appearing at international symposia.
>The world bore witness to her astonishing intellect.
>While Naoto fell from his pedastal.
(I have to keep trying... I have to...)
Uh, Naoto, you okay? Have you been getting enough sleep?
Huh? Me? Yeah, I'm fine...
(My lab mates have begun giving me these looks...)
Naoto, you don't look well. Please, take some time off.
No, I'm okay. I need to get going so...

Uh, alright.
Later, dude.
Naoto's really changed since Shiori joined our group.
Yes, he has. I feel he's lost all confidence in himself.
It's a shame since he has all this talent and gumption to get things done.
But I do worry for him. I really hope nothing happens to him.
>At a conference the next day.
...is what I can conclude from this. Thank you for your time.
Bravo!!!
That was great, Shiori! You had everyone eating out of your hand!
That was too easy.
Please, will you not consider our offer?
(It doesn't matter how hard I try. I can't beat a real genius.)
(Nobody even cares about what I'm researching anymore.)
(Only the best of the best, like Shiori, get to stand in the limelight.)
Nobody would notice if I just disappeared...
>Out of the deafeaning applause, Naoto hears Shinonome's voice.
Hey, Naoto, do you have any interest in joining my group?
Shinonome...?
I thought people only care about Shiori's research...
You numbskull. She's smart, but she's also a crappy human being.
That's why I want you to join my group, Naoto.
I need you for this.
You need me...?
>Naoto's eyes light up with joy.
If you mean that, I'll do whatever I can to help, Shinonome...
Good. I'll be looking forward to your results.
>Present day.
>Somewhere in Tokyo...
What? You failed again?
When exactly do you plan on actually succeeding?

I'm sorry...
Next time, I'm sure I'll...!
Enough.
I've had it with you. You're done.
No, please, wait!
You can't do this without me, right...?
Oh, don't worry about that. You can easily be replaced.
But...
So goodbye.
B-But...!
*Sigh*
>As Naoto wanders aimlessly, a street vendor calls out to him.
Hey, kid, why the long face?
Who the hell are you? Don't talk to me...!
Aww, don't be like that. Come on, check out my wares.
Who knows? You might even find something that can cheer you up.
How can anything here possibly make me feel better...?
Again, quit being such a downer.
>Naoto spots a golden horn and picks it up.
Ah, that is no ordinary horn.
It calls for the end of the world. Ragnarok.
It belongs to one of the gods of Asgard.
But I excel at stealing things that humans would never dream of possessing.
Why do you even have this to begin with...?

*Snicker*
It was but a small trifle.
What do you mean by that...?
I have no idea what's bothering you,
but what if I told you that you could end this world right now?
That trinket there can do just that, you know?
So how about it, kid?
1,000 Macca for the Gjallarhorn.

1,000 Macca...?
Do you mean 1,000 Yen?
Fine, that works too.
A horn that can end the world. You better not be fucking with me...
I'll take it.
>Naoto hands 1,000 Yen over to the street vendor.

*Snicker*
Appreciate it.
I want my money back if this doesn't work. Got it?
>Naoto places his lips on the mouthpiece.
(This world doesn't want me in it...)
(So fuck it! Let's end it...!)
>Naoto takes a deep breath and blows on the horn.
W-What's that noise?!
What's going on?! A siren? No, this sounds like something else...
It sounds like... A horn? No, it's too low, but too high at the same time...
Such an awful sound... I almost feel, scared...
What the hell is this sound?!

I feel... Restless!
I cannot sit still!
This sound... It is making me feel... Excited!
I must do something! It is time to rampage about!
>Naoto stops and everything around him goes silent.
W-What the hell was that...? What the hell is this thing...?
>Naoto looks back towards the street vendor,
>but sees nobody there.
>Naoto stands there dumbfounded,
>while the sound ushering forth the end of the world continues to echo.
